  <COMMENT line1="47" col1="1" line2="47" col2="57" start="10952" end="11008">#' DESeq2 package for differential analysis of count data</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="48" col1="1" line2="48" col2="3" start="11185" end="11187">#' </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="49" col1="1" line2="49" col2="52" start="11418" end="11469">#' The DESeq2 package is designed for normalization,</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="50" col1="1" line2="50" col2="63" start="11651" end="11713">#' visualization, and differential analysis of high-dimensional</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="51" col1="1" line2="51" col2="57" start="11884" end="11940">#' count data. It makes use of empirical Bayes techniques</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="52" col1="1" line2="52" col2="61" start="12117" end="12177">#' to estimate priors for log fold change and dispersion, and</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="53" col1="1" line2="53" col2="57" start="12350" end="12406">#' to calculate posterior estimates for these quantities.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="54" col1="1" line2="54" col2="2" start="12583" end="12584">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="55" col1="1" line2="55" col2="26" start="12816" end="12841">#' The main functions are:</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="56" col1="1" line2="56" col2="2" start="13049" end="13050">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="57" col1="1" line2="57" col2="12" start="13282" end="13293">#' \itemize{</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="58" col1="1" line2="58" col2="108" start="13515" end="13622">#' \item \code{\link{DESeqDataSet}} - build the dataset, see tximeta &amp; tximport packages for preparing input</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="59" col1="1" line2="59" col2="60" start="13748" end="13807">#' \item \code{\link{DESeq}} - perform differential analysis</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="60" col1="1" line2="60" col2="54" start="13981" end="14034">#' \item \code{\link{results}} - build a results table</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="61" col1="1" line2="61" col2="105" start="14214" end="14318">#' \item \code{\link{lfcShrink}} - estimate shrunken LFC (posterior estimates) using apeglm &amp; ashr pakges</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="62" col1="1" line2="62" col2="105" start="14447" end="14551">#' \item \code{\link{vst}} - apply variance stabilizing transformation, e.g. for PCA or sample clustering</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="63" col1="1" line2="63" col2="91" start="14680" end="14770">#' \item Plots, e.g.: \code{\link{plotPCA}}, \code{\link{plotMA}}, \code{\link{plotCounts}}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="64" col1="1" line2="64" col2="4" start="14913" end="14916">#' }</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="65" col1="1" line2="65" col2="3" start="15146" end="15148">#' </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="66" col1="1" line2="66" col2="73" start="15379" end="15451">#' For detailed information on usage, see the package vignette, by typing</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="67" col1="1" line2="67" col2="73" start="15612" end="15684">#' \code{vignette("DESeq2")}, or the workflow linked to on the first page</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="68" col1="1" line2="68" col2="19" start="15845" end="15863">#' of the vignette.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="69" col1="1" line2="69" col2="3" start="16078" end="16080">#' </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="70" col1="1" line2="70" col2="84" start="16311" end="16394">#' All software-related questions should be posted to the Bioconductor Support Site:</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="71" col1="1" line2="71" col2="3" start="16544" end="16546">#' </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="72" col1="1" line2="72" col2="41" start="16777" end="16817">#' \url{https://support.bioconductor.org}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="73" col1="1" line2="73" col2="2" start="17010" end="17011">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="74" col1="1" line2="74" col2="51" start="17243" end="17293">#' The code can be viewed at the GitHub repository,</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="75" col1="1" line2="75" col2="52" start="17476" end="17527">#' which also lists the contributor code of conduct:</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="76" col1="1" line2="76" col2="2" start="17709" end="17710">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="77" col1="1" line2="77" col2="45" start="17942" end="17986">#' \url{https://github.com/mikelove/tximport}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="78" col1="1" line2="78" col2="3" start="18175" end="18177">#' </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="79" col1="1" line2="79" col2="14" start="18408" end="18421">#' @references</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="80" col1="1" line2="80" col2="2" start="18641" end="18642">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="81" col1="1" line2="81" col2="43" start="18874" end="18916">#' Love, M.I., Huber, W., Anders, S. (2014)</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="82" col1="1" line2="82" col2="53" start="19107" end="19159">#' Moderated estimation of fold change and dispersion</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="83" col1="1" line2="83" col2="56" start="19340" end="19395">#' for RNA-seq data with DESeq2. Genome Biology, 15:550.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="84" col1="1" line2="84" col2="50" start="19573" end="19622">#' \url{https://doi.org/10.1186/s13059-014-0550-8}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="85" col1="1" line2="85" col2="2" start="19806" end="19807">#'</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="87" col1="1" line2="87" col2="3" start="20272" end="20274">#' </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="88" col1="1" line2="88" col2="19" start="20505" end="20523">#' @docType package</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="89" col1="1" line2="89" col2="23" start="20738" end="20760">#' @name DESeq2-package</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="90" col1="1" line2="90" col2="26" start="20971" end="20996">#' @aliases DESeq2-package</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="94" col1="1" line2="94" col2="102" start="21903" end="22004">#' Differential expression analysis based on the Negative Binomial (a.k.a. Gamma-Poisson) distribution</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="95" col1="1" line2="95" col2="2" start="22136" end="22137">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="96" col1="1" line2="96" col2="63" start="22369" end="22431">#' This function performs a default analysis through the steps:</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="97" col1="1" line2="97" col2="14" start="22602" end="22615">#' \enumerate{</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="98" col1="1" line2="98" col2="70" start="22835" end="22904">#' \item estimation of size factors: \code{\link{estimateSizeFactors}}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="99" col1="1" line2="99" col2="68" start="23068" end="23135">#' \item estimation of dispersion: \code{\link{estimateDispersions}}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="100" col1="1" line2="100" col2="88" start="23301" end="23388">#' \item Negative Binomial GLM fitting and Wald statistics: \code{\link{nbinomWaldTest}}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="101" col1="1" line2="101" col2="4" start="23534" end="23537">#' }</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="102" col1="1" line2="102" col2="76" start="23767" end="23842">#' For complete details on each step, see the manual pages of the respective</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="103" col1="1" line2="103" col2="76" start="24000" end="24075">#' functions. After the \code{DESeq} function returns a DESeqDataSet object,</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="104" col1="1" line2="104" col2="67" start="24233" end="24299">#' results tables (log2 fold changes and p-values) can be generated</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="105" col1="1" line2="105" col2="44" start="24466" end="24509">#' using the \code{\link{results}} function.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="106" col1="1" line2="106" col2="82" start="24699" end="24780">#' Shrunken LFC can then be generated using the \code{\link{lfcShrink}} function. </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="107" col1="1" line2="107" col2="61" start="24932" end="24992">#' All support questions should be posted to the Bioconductor</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="108" col1="1" line2="108" col2="55" start="25165" end="25219">#' support site: \url{http://support.bioconductor.org}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="109" col1="1" line2="109" col2="2" start="25398" end="25399">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="110" col1="1" line2="110" col2="84" start="25631" end="25714">#' The differential expression analysis uses a generalized linear model of the form:</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="111" col1="1" line2="111" col2="2" start="25864" end="25865">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="112" col1="1" line2="112" col2="85" start="26097" end="26181">#' \deqn{ K_{ij} \sim \textrm{NB}( \mu_{ij}, \alpha_i) }{ K_ij ~ NB(mu_ij, alpha_i) }</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="113" col1="1" line2="113" col2="53" start="26330" end="26382">#' \deqn{ \mu_{ij} = s_j q_{ij} }{ mu_ij = s_j q_ij }</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="114" col1="1" line2="114" col2="71" start="26563" end="26633">#' \deqn{ \log_2(q_{ij}) = x_{j.} \beta_i }{ log2(q_ij) = x_j. beta_i }</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="115" col1="1" line2="115" col2="2" start="26796" end="26797">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="116" col1="1" line2="116" col2="73" start="27029" end="27101">#' where counts \eqn{K_{ij}}{K_ij} for gene i, sample j are modeled using</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="117" col1="1" line2="117" col2="74" start="27262" end="27335">#' a Negative Binomial distribution with fitted mean \eqn{\mu_{ij}}{mu_ij}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="118" col1="1" line2="118" col2="68" start="27495" end="27562">#' and a gene-specific dispersion parameter \eqn{\alpha_i}{alpha_i}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="119" col1="1" line2="119" col2="63" start="27728" end="27790">#' The fitted mean is composed of a sample-specific size factor</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="120" col1="1" line2="120" col2="72" start="27961" end="28032">#' \eqn{s_j}{s_j} and a parameter \eqn{q_{ij}}{q_ij} proportional to the</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="121" col1="1" line2="121" col2="57" start="28194" end="28250">#' expected true concentration of fragments for sample j.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="122" col1="1" line2="122" col2="88" start="28427" end="28514">#' The coefficients \eqn{\beta_i}{beta_i} give the log2 fold changes for gene i for each</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="123" col1="1" line2="123" col2="41" start="28660" end="28700">#' column of the model matrix \eqn{X}{X}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="124" col1="1" line2="124" col2="54" start="28893" end="28946">#' The sample-specific size factors can be replaced by</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="125" col1="1" line2="125" col2="60" start="29126" end="29185">#' gene-specific normalization factors for each sample using</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="126" col1="1" line2="126" col2="38" start="29359" end="29396">#' \code{\link{normalizationFactors}}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="127" col1="1" line2="127" col2="2" start="29592" end="29593">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="128" col1="1" line2="128" col2="83" start="29825" end="29907">#' For details on the fitting of the log2 fold changes and calculation of p-values,</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="129" col1="1" line2="129" col2="64" start="30058" end="30121">#' see \code{\link{nbinomWaldTest}} if using \code{test="Wald"},</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="130" col1="1" line2="130" col2="57" start="30291" end="30347">#' or \code{\link{nbinomLRT}} if using \code{test="LRT"}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="131" col1="1" line2="131" col2="2" start="30524" end="30525">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="132" col1="1" line2="132" col2="79" start="30757" end="30835">#' Experiments without replicates do not allow for estimation of the dispersion</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="133" col1="1" line2="133" col2="76" start="30990" end="31065">#' of counts around the expected value for each group, which is critical for</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="134" col1="1" line2="134" col2="79" start="31223" end="31301">#' differential expression analysis. Analysis without replicates was deprecated</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="135" col1="1" line2="135" col2="51" start="31456" end="31506">#' in v1.20 and is no longer supported since v1.22.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="136" col1="1" line2="136" col2="3" start="31689" end="31691">#' </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="137" col1="1" line2="137" col2="78" start="31922" end="31999">#' The argument \code{minReplicatesForReplace} is used to decide which samples</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="138" col1="1" line2="138" col2="81" start="32155" end="32235">#' are eligible for automatic replacement in the case of extreme Cook's distance.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="139" col1="1" line2="139" col2="75" start="32388" end="32462">#' By default, \code{DESeq} will replace outliers if the Cook's distance is</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="140" col1="1" line2="140" col2="72" start="32621" end="32692">#' large for a sample which has 7 or more replicates (including itself).</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="141" col1="1" line2="141" col2="77" start="32854" end="32930">#' Outlier replacement is turned off entirely for \code{fitType="glmGamPoi"}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="142" col1="1" line2="142" col2="69" start="33087" end="33155">#' This replacement is performed by the \code{\link{replaceOutliers}}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="143" col1="1" line2="143" col2="67" start="33320" end="33386">#' function. This default behavior helps to prevent filtering genes</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="144" col1="1" line2="144" col2="67" start="33553" end="33619">#' based on Cook's distance when there are many degrees of freedom.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="145" col1="1" line2="145" col2="71" start="33786" end="33856">#' See \code{\link{results}} for more information about filtering using</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="146" col1="1" line2="146" col2="76" start="34019" end="34094">#' Cook's distance, and the 'Dealing with outliers' section of the vignette.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="147" col1="1" line2="147" col2="81" start="34252" end="34332">#' Unlike the behavior of \code{\link{replaceOutliers}}, here original counts are</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="148" col1="1" line2="148" col2="71" start="34485" end="34555">#' kept in the matrix returned by \code{\link{counts}}, original Cook's</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="149" col1="1" line2="149" col2="75" start="34718" end="34792">#' distances are kept in \code{assays(dds)[["cooks"]]}, and the replacement</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="150" col1="1" line2="150" col2="77" start="34951" end="35027">#' counts used for fitting are kept in \code{assays(dds)[["replaceCounts"]]}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="151" col1="1" line2="151" col2="2" start="35184" end="35185">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="152" col1="1" line2="152" col2="65" start="35417" end="35481">#' Note that if a log2 fold change prior is used (betaPrior=TRUE)</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="153" col1="1" line2="153" col2="66" start="35650" end="35715">#' then expanded model matrices will be used in fitting. These are</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="154" col1="1" line2="154" col2="69" start="35883" end="35951">#' described in \code{\link{nbinomWaldTest}} and in the vignette. The</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="155" col1="1" line2="155" col2="71" start="36116" end="36186">#' \code{contrast} argument of \code{\link{results}} should be used for</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="156" col1="1" line2="156" col2="29" start="36349" end="36377">#' generating results tables.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="157" col1="1" line2="157" col2="3" start="36582" end="36584">#' </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="158" col1="1" line2="158" col2="69" start="36815" end="36883">#' @return a \code{\link{DESeqDataSet}} object with results stored as</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="159" col1="1" line2="159" col2="87" start="37048" end="37134">#' metadata columns. These results should accessed by calling the \code{\link{results}}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="160" col1="1" line2="160" col2="88" start="37281" end="37368">#' function. By default this will return the log2 fold changes and p-values for the last</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="161" col1="1" line2="161" col2="87" start="37514" end="37600">#' variable in the design formula.  See \code{\link{results}} for how to access results</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="162" col1="1" line2="162" col2="23" start="37747" end="37769">#' for other variables.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="163" col1="1" line2="163" col2="2" start="37980" end="37981">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="164" col1="1" line2="164" col2="69" start="38213" end="38281">#' @param object a DESeqDataSet object, see the constructor functions</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="165" col1="1" line2="165" col2="30" start="38446" end="38475">#' \code{\link{DESeqDataSet}},</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="166" col1="1" line2="166" col2="40" start="38679" end="38718">#' \code{\link{DESeqDataSetFromMatrix}},</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="167" col1="1" line2="167" col2="44" start="38912" end="38955">#' \code{\link{DESeqDataSetFromHTSeqCount}}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="168" col1="1" line2="168" col2="66" start="39145" end="39210">#' @param test either "Wald" or "LRT", which will then use either </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="169" col1="1" line2="169" col2="69" start="39378" end="39446">#' Wald significance tests (defined by \code{\link{nbinomWaldTest}}),</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="170" col1="1" line2="170" col2="71" start="39611" end="39681">#' or the likelihood ratio test on the difference in deviance between a</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="171" col1="1" line2="171" col2="70" start="39844" end="39913">#' full and reduced model formula (defined by \code{\link{nbinomLRT}})</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="172" col1="1" line2="172" col2="70" start="40077" end="40146">#' @param fitType either "parametric", "local", "mean", or "glmGamPoi"</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="173" col1="1" line2="173" col2="64" start="40310" end="40373">#' for the type of fitting of dispersions to the mean intensity.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="174" col1="1" line2="174" col2="57" start="40543" end="40599">#' See \code{\link{estimateDispersions}} for description.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="175" col1="1" line2="175" col2="58" start="40776" end="40833">#' @param sfType either "ratio", "poscounts", or "iterate"</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="176" col1="1" line2="176" col2="46" start="41009" end="41054">#' for the type of size factor estimation. See</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="177" col1="1" line2="177" col2="54" start="41242" end="41295">#' \code{\link{estimateSizeFactors}} for description. </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="178" col1="1" line2="178" col2="69" start="41475" end="41543">#' @param betaPrior whether or not to put a zero-mean normal prior on</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="179" col1="1" line2="179" col2="34" start="41708" end="41741">#' the non-intercept coefficients </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="180" col1="1" line2="180" col2="70" start="41941" end="42010">#' See \code{\link{nbinomWaldTest}} for description of the calculation</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="181" col1="1" line2="181" col2="67" start="42174" end="42240">#' of the beta prior. In versions \code{&gt;=1.16}, the default is set</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="182" col1="1" line2="182" col2="67" start="42407" end="42473">#' to \code{FALSE}, and shrunken LFCs are obtained afterwards using</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="183" col1="1" line2="183" col2="27" start="42640" end="42666">#' \code{\link{lfcShrink}}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="184" col1="1" line2="184" col2="61" start="42873" end="42933">#' @param full for \code{test="LRT"}, the full model formula,</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="185" col1="1" line2="185" col2="63" start="43106" end="43168">#' which is restricted to the formula in \code{design(object)}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="186" col1="1" line2="186" col2="67" start="43339" end="43405">#' alternatively, it can be a model matrix constructed by the user.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="187" col1="1" line2="187" col2="74" start="43572" end="43645">#' advanced use: specifying a model matrix for full and \code{test="Wald"}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="188" col1="1" line2="188" col2="40" start="43805" end="43844">#' is possible if \code{betaPrior=FALSE}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="189" col1="1" line2="189" col2="78" start="44038" end="44115">#' @param reduced for \code{test="LRT"}, a reduced formula to compare against,</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="190" col1="1" line2="190" col2="63" start="44271" end="44333">#' i.e., the full formula with the term(s) of interest removed.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="191" col1="1" line2="191" col2="66" start="44504" end="44569">#' alternatively, it can be a model matrix constructed by the user</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="192" col1="1" line2="192" col2="54" start="44737" end="44790">#' @param quiet whether to print messages at each step</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="193" col1="1" line2="193" col2="75" start="44970" end="45044">#' @param minReplicatesForReplace the minimum number of replicates required</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="194" col1="1" line2="194" col2="53" start="45203" end="45255">#' in order to use \code{\link{replaceOutliers}} on a</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="195" col1="1" line2="195" col2="71" start="45436" end="45506">#' sample. If there are samples with so many replicates, the model will</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="196" col1="1" line2="196" col2="71" start="45669" end="45739">#' be refit after these replacing outliers, flagged by Cook's distance.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="197" col1="1" line2="197" col2="56" start="45902" end="45957">#' Set to \code{Inf} in order to never replace outliers.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="198" col1="1" line2="198" col2="55" start="46135" end="46189">#' It set to \code{Inf} for \code{fitType="glmGamPoi"}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="199" col1="1" line2="199" col2="73" start="46368" end="46440">#' @param modelMatrixType either "standard" or "expanded", which describe</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="200" col1="1" line2="200" col2="56" start="46601" end="46656">#' how the model matrix, X of the GLM formula is formed.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="201" col1="1" line2="201" col2="60" start="46834" end="46893">#' "standard" is as created by \code{model.matrix} using the</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="202" col1="1" line2="202" col2="69" start="47067" end="47135">#' design formula. "expanded" includes an indicator variable for each</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="203" col1="1" line2="203" col2="69" start="47300" end="47368">#' level of factors in addition to an intercept. for more information</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="204" col1="1" line2="204" col2="55" start="47533" end="47587">#' see the Description of \code{\link{nbinomWaldTest}}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="205" col1="1" line2="205" col2="69" start="47766" end="47834">#' betaPrior must be set to TRUE in order for expanded model matrices</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="206" col1="1" line2="206" col2="13" start="47999" end="48011">#' to be fit.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="207" col1="1" line2="207" col2="81" start="48232" end="48312">#' @param useT logical, passed to \code{\link{nbinomWaldTest}}, default is FALSE,</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="208" col1="1" line2="208" col2="64" start="48465" end="48528">#' where Wald statistics are assumed to follow a standard Normal</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="209" col1="1" line2="209" col2="83" start="48698" end="48780">#' @param minmu lower bound on the estimated count for fitting gene-wise dispersion</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="210" col1="1" line2="210" col2="63" start="48931" end="48993">#' and for use with \code{nbinomWaldTest} and \code{nbinomLRT}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="211" col1="1" line2="211" col2="56" start="49164" end="49219">#' If \code{fitType="glmGamPoi"}, then 1e-6 will be used</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="212" col1="1" line2="212" col2="68" start="49397" end="49464">#' (as this fitType is optimized for single cell data, where a lower</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="213" col1="1" line2="213" col2="53" start="49630" end="49682">#' minmu is recommended), otherwise the default value</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="214" col1="1" line2="214" col2="39" start="49863" end="49901">#' as evaluated on bulk datasets is 0.5</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="215" col1="1" line2="215" col2="66" start="50096" end="50161">#' @param parallel if FALSE, no parallelization. if TRUE, parallel</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="216" col1="1" line2="216" col2="73" start="50329" end="50401">#' execution using \code{BiocParallel}, see next argument \code{BPPARAM}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="217" col1="1" line2="217" col2="62" start="50562" end="50623">#' Two notes on running in parallel using \code{BiocParallel}:</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="218" col1="1" line2="218" col2="66" start="50795" end="50860">#' 1) it is recommended to filter out genes where all samples have</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="219" col1="1" line2="219" col2="73" start="51028" end="51100">#' low counts before running DESeq2 in parellel: this improves efficiency</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="220" col1="1" line2="220" col2="73" start="51261" end="51333">#' as otherwise you will be sending data to child processes, though those</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="221" col1="1" line2="221" col2="69" start="51494" end="51562">#' have little power for detection of differences, and will likely be</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="222" col1="1" line2="222" col2="43" start="51727" end="51769">#' removed by independent filtering anyway;</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="223" col1="1" line2="223" col2="15" start="51960" end="51974">#' 2) it may be</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="224" col1="1" line2="224" col2="67" start="52193" end="52259">#' advantageous to remove large, unneeded objects from your current</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="225" col1="1" line2="225" col2="45" start="52426" end="52470">#' R environment before calling \code{DESeq},</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="226" col1="1" line2="226" col2="57" start="52659" end="52715">#' as it is possible that R's internal garbage collection</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="227" col1="1" line2="227" col2="55" start="52892" end="52946">#' will copy these files while running on worker nodes.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="228" col1="1" line2="228" col2="64" start="53125" end="53188">#' @param BPPARAM an optional parameter object passed internally</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="229" col1="1" line2="229" col2="55" start="53358" end="53412">#' to \code{\link{bplapply}} when \code{parallel=TRUE}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="230" col1="1" line2="230" col2="56" start="53591" end="53646">#' If not specified, the parameters last registered with</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="231" col1="1" line2="231" col2="39" start="53824" end="53862">#' \code{\link{register}} will be used.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="232" col1="1" line2="232" col2="3" start="54057" end="54059">#' </COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="433" col1="1" line2="433" col2="32" start="100890" end="100921">#' Make a simulated DESeqDataSet</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="434" col1="1" line2="434" col2="2" start="101123" end="101124">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="435" col1="1" line2="435" col2="64" start="101356" end="101419">#' Constructs a simulated dataset of Negative Binomial data from</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="436" col1="1" line2="436" col2="64" start="101589" end="101652">#' two conditions. By default, there are no fold changes between</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="437" col1="1" line2="437" col2="80" start="101822" end="101901">#' the two conditions, but this can be adjusted with the \code{betaSD} argument.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="438" col1="1" line2="438" col2="2" start="102055" end="102056">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="439" col1="1" line2="439" col2="26" start="102288" end="102313">#' @param n number of rows</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="440" col1="1" line2="440" col2="29" start="102521" end="102549">#' @param m number of columns</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="441" col1="1" line2="441" col2="88" start="102754" end="102841">#' @param betaSD the standard deviation for non-intercept betas, i.e. beta ~ N(0,betaSD)</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="442" col1="1" line2="442" col2="68" start="102987" end="103054">#' @param interceptMean the mean of the intercept betas (log2 scale)</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="443" col1="1" line2="443" col2="80" start="103220" end="103299">#' @param interceptSD the standard deviation of the intercept betas (log2 scale)</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="444" col1="1" line2="444" col2="82" start="103453" end="103534">#' @param dispMeanRel a function specifying the relationship of the dispersions on</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="445" col1="1" line2="445" col2="25" start="103686" end="103710">#' \code{2^trueIntercept}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="446" col1="1" line2="446" col2="60" start="103919" end="103978">#' @param sizeFactors multiplicative factors for each sample</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="448" col1="1" line2="448" col2="61" start="104385" end="104445">#' @return a \code{\link{DESeqDataSet}} with true dispersion,</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="449" col1="1" line2="449" col2="73" start="104618" end="104690">#' intercept and beta values in the metadata columns.  Note that the true</COMMENT>

            </expr>
          </expr>

  <COMMENT line1="500" col1="1" line2="500" col2="70" start="116501" end="116570">#' Low-level function to estimate size factors with robust regression.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="501" col1="1" line2="501" col2="3" start="116734" end="116736">#' </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="502" col1="1" line2="502" col2="79" start="116967" end="117045">#' Given a matrix or data frame of count data, this function estimates the size</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="503" col1="1" line2="503" col2="75" start="117200" end="117274">#' factors as follows: Each column is divided by the geometric means of the</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="504" col1="1" line2="504" col2="75" start="117433" end="117507">#' rows. The median (or, if requested, another location estimator) of these</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="505" col1="1" line2="505" col2="80" start="117666" end="117745">#' ratios (skipping the genes with a geometric mean of zero) is used as the size</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="506" col1="1" line2="506" col2="87" start="117899" end="117985">#' factor for this column. Typically, one will not call this function directly, but use</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="507" col1="1" line2="507" col2="37" start="118132" end="118168">#' \code{\link{estimateSizeFactors}}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="508" col1="1" line2="508" col2="3" start="118365" end="118367">#' </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="509" col1="1" line2="509" col2="77" start="118598" end="118674">#' @param counts a matrix or data frame of counts, i.e., non-negative integer</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="510" col1="1" line2="510" col2="9" start="118831" end="118839">#' values</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="511" col1="1" line2="511" col2="80" start="119064" end="119143">#' @param locfunc a function to compute a location for a sample. By default, the</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="512" col1="1" line2="512" col2="58" start="119297" end="119354">#' median is used. However, especially for low counts, the</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="513" col1="1" line2="513" col2="85" start="119530" end="119614">#' \code{\link[genefilter]{shorth}} function from genefilter may give better results.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="514" col1="1" line2="514" col2="59" start="119763" end="119821">#' @param geoMeans by default this is not provided, and the</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="515" col1="1" line2="515" col2="68" start="119996" end="120063">#' geometric means of the counts are calculated within the function.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="516" col1="1" line2="516" col2="72" start="120229" end="120300">#' A vector of geometric means from another count matrix can be provided</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="517" col1="1" line2="517" col2="41" start="120462" end="120502">#' for a "frozen" size factor calculation</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="518" col1="1" line2="518" col2="90" start="120695" end="120784">#' @param controlGenes optional, numeric or logical index vector specifying those genes to</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="519" col1="1" line2="519" col2="71" start="120928" end="120998">#' use for size factor estimation (e.g. housekeeping or spike-in genes)</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="520" col1="1" line2="520" col2="66" start="121161" end="121226">#' @param type standard median ratio (\code{"ratio"}) or where the</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="521" col1="1" line2="521" col2="65" start="121394" end="121458">#' geometric mean is only calculated over positive counts per row</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="522" col1="1" line2="522" col2="23" start="121627" end="121649">#' (\code{"poscounts"})</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="523" col1="1" line2="523" col2="75" start="121860" end="121934">#' @return a vector with the estimates size factors, one element per column</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="524" col1="1" line2="524" col2="23" start="122093" end="122115">#' @author Simon Anders</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="525" col1="1" line2="525" col2="45" start="122326" end="122370">#' @seealso \code{\link{estimateSizeFactors}}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="526" col1="1" line2="526" col2="12" start="122559" end="122570">#' @examples</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="579" col1="1" line2="579" col2="50" start="134908" end="134957">#' Low-level functions to fit dispersion estimates</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="580" col1="1" line2="580" col2="2" start="135141" end="135142">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="581" col1="1" line2="581" col2="69" start="135374" end="135442">#' Normal users should instead use \code{\link{estimateDispersions}}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="582" col1="1" line2="582" col2="77" start="135607" end="135683">#' These low-level functions are called by \code{\link{estimateDispersions}},</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="583" col1="1" line2="583" col2="58" start="135840" end="135897">#' but are exported and documented for non-standard usage.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="584" col1="1" line2="584" col2="87" start="136073" end="136159">#' For instance, it is possible to replace fitted values with a custom fit and continue</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="585" col1="1" line2="585" col2="78" start="136306" end="136383">#' with the maximum a posteriori dispersion estimation, as demonstrated in the</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="586" col1="1" line2="586" col2="18" start="136539" end="136556">#' examples below.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="587" col1="1" line2="587" col2="2" start="136772" end="136773">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="588" col1="1" line2="588" col2="31" start="137005" end="137035">#' @param object a DESeqDataSet</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="589" col1="1" line2="589" col2="70" start="137238" end="137307">#' @param fitType either "parametric", "local", "mean", or "glmGamPoi"</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="590" col1="1" line2="590" col2="64" start="137471" end="137534">#' for the type of fitting of dispersions to the mean intensity.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="591" col1="1" line2="591" col2="57" start="137704" end="137760">#' See \code{\link{estimateDispersions}} for description.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="592" col1="1" line2="592" col2="60" start="137937" end="137996">#' @param outlierSD the number of standard deviations of log</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="593" col1="1" line2="593" col2="59" start="138170" end="138228">#' gene-wise estimates above the prior mean (fitted value),</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="594" col1="1" line2="594" col2="52" start="138403" end="138454">#' above which dispersion estimates will be labelled</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="595" col1="1" line2="595" col2="56" start="138636" end="138691">#' outliers. Outliers will keep their original value and</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="596" col1="1" line2="596" col2="33" start="138869" end="138901">#' not be shrunk using the prior.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="597" col1="1" line2="597" col2="79" start="139102" end="139180">#' @param dispPriorVar the variance of the normal prior on the log dispersions.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="598" col1="1" line2="598" col2="64" start="139335" end="139398">#' If not supplied, this is calculated as the difference between</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="599" col1="1" line2="599" col2="59" start="139568" end="139626">#' the mean squared residuals of gene-wise estimates to the</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="600" col1="1" line2="600" col2="55" start="139801" end="139855">#' fitted dispersion and the expected sampling variance</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="601" col1="1" line2="601" col2="24" start="140034" end="140057">#' of the log dispersion</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="602" col1="1" line2="602" col2="66" start="140267" end="140332">#' @param minDisp small value for the minimum dispersion, to allow</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="603" col1="1" line2="603" col2="81" start="140500" end="140580">#' for calculations in log scale, one order of magnitude above this value is used</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="604" col1="1" line2="604" col2="53" start="140733" end="140785">#' as a test for inclusion in mean-dispersion fitting</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="605" col1="1" line2="605" col2="72" start="140966" end="141037">#' @param kappa_0 control parameter used in setting the initial proposal</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="606" col1="1" line2="606" col2="65" start="141199" end="141263">#' in backtracking search, higher kappa_0 results in larger steps</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="607" col1="1" line2="607" col2="78" start="141432" end="141509">#' @param dispTol control parameter to test for convergence of log dispersion,</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="608" col1="1" line2="608" col2="59" start="141665" end="141723">#' stop when increase in log posterior is less than dispTol</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="609" col1="1" line2="609" col2="88" start="141898" end="141985">#' @param maxit control parameter: maximum number of iterations to allow for convergence</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="610" col1="1" line2="610" col2="50" start="142131" end="142180">#' @param useCR whether to use Cox-Reid correction</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="611" col1="1" line2="611" col2="84" start="142364" end="142447">#' @param weightThreshold threshold for subsetting the design matrix and GLM weights</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="612" col1="1" line2="612" col2="42" start="142597" end="142638">#' for calculating the Cox-Reid correction</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="613" col1="1" line2="613" col2="54" start="142830" end="142883">#' @param quiet whether to print messages at each step</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="614" col1="1" line2="614" col2="44" start="143063" end="143106">#' @param modelMatrix for advanced use only,</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="615" col1="1" line2="615" col2="72" start="143296" end="143367">#' a substitute model matrix for gene-wise and MAP dispersion estimation</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="616" col1="1" line2="616" col2="74" start="143529" end="143602">#' @param niter number of times to iterate between estimation of means and</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="617" col1="1" line2="617" col2="27" start="143762" end="143788">#' estimation of dispersion</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="618" col1="1" line2="618" col2="76" start="143995" end="144070">#' @param linearMu estimate the expected counts matrix using a linear model,</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="619" col1="1" line2="619" col2="63" start="144228" end="144290">#' default is NULL, in which case a lienar model is used if the</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="620" col1="1" line2="620" col2="70" start="144461" end="144530">#' number of groups defined by the model matrix is equal to the number</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="621" col1="1" line2="621" col2="33" start="144694" end="144726">#' of columns of the model matrix</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="622" col1="1" line2="622" col2="83" start="144927" end="145009">#' @param minmu lower bound on the estimated count for fitting gene-wise dispersion</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="623" col1="1" line2="623" col2="68" start="145160" end="145227">#' @param alphaInit initial guess for the dispersion estimate, alpha</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="624" col1="1" line2="624" col2="80" start="145393" end="145472">#' @param type can either be "DESeq2" or "glmGamPoi". Specifies if the glmGamPoi</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="625" col1="1" line2="625" col2="80" start="145626" end="145705">#' package is used to calculate the dispersion. This can be significantly faster</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="626" col1="1" line2="626" col2="50" start="145859" end="145908">#' if there are many replicates with small counts.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="627" col1="1" line2="627" col2="3" start="146092" end="146094">#' </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="628" col1="1" line2="628" col2="62" start="146325" end="146386">#' @return a DESeqDataSet with gene-wise, fitted, or final MAP</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="629" col1="1" line2="629" col2="62" start="146558" end="146619">#' dispersion estimates in the metadata columns of the object.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="630" col1="1" line2="630" col2="3" start="146791" end="146793">#' </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="631" col1="1" line2="631" col2="87" start="147024" end="147110">#' \code{estimateDispersionsPriorVar} is called inside of \code{estimateDispersionsMAP}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="632" col1="1" line2="632" col2="62" start="147257" end="147318">#' and stores the dispersion prior variance as an attribute of</COMMENT>

                  <SYMBOL_FUNCTION_CALL line1="1181" col1="22" line2="1181" col2="29" start="275195" end="275202">trigamma</SYMBOL_FUNCTION_CALL>
                </expr>
                <OP-LEFT-PAREN line1="1181" col1="30" line2="1181" col2="30" start="275203" end="275203">(</OP-LEFT-PAREN>
                <expr line1="1181" col1="31" line2="1181" col2="39" start="275204" end="275212">
                  <expr line1="1181" col1="31" line2="1181" col2="37" start="275204" end="275210">
                    <OP-LEFT-PAREN line1="1181" col1="31" line2="1181" col2="31" start="275204" end="275204">(</OP-LEFT-PAREN>
                    <expr line1="1181" col1="32" line2="1181" col2="36" start="275205" end="275209">
                      <expr line1="1181" col1="32" line2="1181" col2="32" start="275205" end="275205">
                        <SYMBOL line1="1181" col1="32" line2="1181" col2="32" start="275205" end="275205">m</SYMBOL>
                      </expr>
                      <OP-MINUS line1="1181" col1="34" line2="1181" col2="34" start="275207" end="275207">-</OP-MINUS>
                      <expr line1="1181" col1="36" line2="1181" col2="36" start="275209" end="275209">
                        <SYMBOL line1="1181" col1="36" line2="1181" col2="36" start="275209" end="275209">p</SYMBOL>
                      </expr>
                    </expr>
                    <OP-RIGHT-PAREN line1="1181" col1="37" line2="1181" col2="37" start="275210" end="275210">)</OP-RIGHT-PAREN>
                  </expr>
                  <OP-SLASH line1="1181" col1="38" line2="1181" col2="38" start="275211" end="275211">/</OP-SLASH>
                  <expr line1="1181" col1="39" line2="1181" col2="39" start="275212" end="275212">
                    <NUM_CONST line1="1181" col1="39" line2="1181" col2="39" start="275212" end="275212">2</NUM_CONST>
                  </expr>
                </expr>
                <OP-RIGHT-PAREN line1="1181" col1="40" line2="1181" col2="40" start="275213" end="275213">)</OP-RIGHT-PAREN>
              </expr>
            </expr>
            <COMMENT line1="1182" col1="5" line2="1182" col2="61" start="275411" end="275467"># set the variance of the prior using these two estimates</COMMENT>
            <COMMENT line1="1183" col1="5" line2="1183" col2="27" start="275644" end="275666"># with a minimum of .25</COMMENT>
            <expr line1="1184" col1="5" line2="1184" col2="64" start="275877" end="275936">
              <expr line1="1184" col1="5" line2="1184" col2="16" start="275877" end="275888">
                <SYMBOL line1="1184" col1="5" line2="1184" col2="16" start="275877" end="275888">dispPriorVar</SYMBOL>
              </expr>
              <LEFT_ASSIGN line1="1184" col1="18" line2="1184" col2="19" start="275890" end="275891">&lt;-</LEFT_ASSIGN>
              <expr line1="1184" col1="21" line2="1184" col2="64" start="275893" end="275936">
                <expr line1="1184" col1="21" line2="1184" col2="24" start="275893" end="275896">
                  <SYMBOL_FUNCTION_CALL line1="1184" col1="21" line2="1184" col2="24" start="275893" end="275896">pmax</SYMBOL_FUNCTION_CALL>
                </expr>
                <OP-LEFT-PAREN line1="1184" col1="25" line2="1184" col2="25" start="275897" end="275897">(</OP-LEFT-PAREN>
                <expr line1="1184" col1="26" line2="1184" col2="57" start="275898" end="275929">
                  <OP-LEFT-PAREN line1="1184" col1="26" line2="1184" col2="26" start="275898" end="275898">(</OP-LEFT-PAREN>
                  <expr line1="1184" col1="27" line2="1184" col2="56" start="275899" end="275928">
                    <expr line1="1184" col1="27" line2="1184" col2="40" start="275899" end="275912">
                      <SYMBOL line1="1184" col1="27" line2="1184" col2="40" start="275899" end="275912">varLogDispEsts</SYMBOL>
                    </expr>
                    <OP-MINUS line1="1184" col1="42" line2="1184" col2="42" start="275914" end="275914">-</OP-MINUS>

                </expr>
                <OP-COMMA line1="1184" col1="58" line2="1184" col2="58" start="275930" end="275930">,</OP-COMMA>
                <expr line1="1184" col1="60" line2="1184" col2="63" start="275932" end="275935">

            </expr>
            <OP-RIGHT-BRACE line1="1185" col1="3" line2="1185" col2="3" start="276108" end="276108">}</OP-RIGHT-BRACE>
          </expr>
          <ELSE line1="1185" col1="5" line2="1185" col2="8" start="276110" end="276113">else</ELSE>
          <expr line1="1185" col1="10" line2="1189" col2="3" start="276115" end="277040">
            <OP-LEFT-BRACE line1="1185" col1="10" line2="1185" col2="10" start="276115" end="276115">{</OP-LEFT-BRACE>
            <COMMENT line1="1186" col1="5" line2="1186" col2="64" start="276343" end="276402"># we have m = p, so do not try to subtract sampling variance</COMMENT>
            <expr line1="1187" col1="5" line2="1187" col2="34" start="276576" end="276605">
              <expr line1="1187" col1="5" line2="1187" col2="16" start="276576" end="276587">

            </expr>
            <expr line1="1188" col1="5" line2="1188" col2="22" start="276809" end="276826">

    </expr>
  </expr>
  <COMMENT line1="1196" col1="1" line2="1196" col2="37" start="278669" end="278705">#' Wald test for the GLM coefficients</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1197" col1="1" line2="1197" col2="3" start="278902" end="278904">#' </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1198" col1="1" line2="1198" col2="69" start="279135" end="279203">#' This function tests for significance of coefficients in a Negative</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1199" col1="1" line2="1199" col2="70" start="279368" end="279437">#' Binomial GLM, using previously calculated \code{\link{sizeFactors}}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1200" col1="1" line2="1200" col2="42" start="279601" end="279642">#' (or \code{\link{normalizationFactors}})</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1201" col1="1" line2="1201" col2="74" start="279834" end="279907">#' and dispersion estimates.  See \code{\link{DESeq}} for the GLM formula.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1202" col1="1" line2="1202" col2="3" start="280067" end="280069">#' </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1203" col1="1" line2="1203" col2="73" start="280300" end="280372">#' The fitting proceeds as follows: standard maximum likelihood estimates</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1204" col1="1" line2="1204" col2="83" start="280533" end="280615">#' for GLM coefficients (synonymous with "beta", "log2 fold change", "effect size")</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1205" col1="1" line2="1205" col2="18" start="280766" end="280783">#' are calculated.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1206" col1="1" line2="1206" col2="63" start="280999" end="281061">#' Then, optionally, a zero-centered Normal prior distribution </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1207" col1="1" line2="1207" col2="79" start="281232" end="281310">#' (\code{betaPrior}) is assumed for the coefficients other than the intercept.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1208" col1="1" line2="1208" col2="2" start="281465" end="281466">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1209" col1="1" line2="1209" col2="44" start="281698" end="281741">#' Note that this posterior log2 fold change</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1210" col1="1" line2="1210" col2="71" start="281931" end="282001">#' estimation is now not the default setting for \code{nbinomWaldTest},</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1211" col1="1" line2="1211" col2="66" start="282164" end="282229">#' as the standard workflow for coefficient shrinkage has moved to</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1212" col1="1" line2="1212" col2="49" start="282397" end="282445">#' an additional function \code{link{lfcShrink}}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1213" col1="1" line2="1213" col2="2" start="282630" end="282631">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1214" col1="1" line2="1214" col2="75" start="282863" end="282937">#' For calculating Wald test p-values, the coefficients are scaled by their</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1215" col1="1" line2="1215" col2="72" start="283096" end="283167">#' standard errors and then compared to a standard Normal distribution. </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1216" col1="1" line2="1216" col2="28" start="283329" end="283356">#' The \code{\link{results}}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1217" col1="1" line2="1217" col2="78" start="283562" end="283639">#' function without any arguments will automatically perform a contrast of the</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1218" col1="1" line2="1218" col2="78" start="283795" end="283872">#' last level of the last variable in the design formula over the first level.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1219" col1="1" line2="1219" col2="81" start="284028" end="284108">#' The \code{contrast} argument of the \code{\link{results}} function can be used</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1220" col1="1" line2="1220" col2="33" start="284261" end="284293">#' to generate other comparisons.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1221" col1="1" line2="1221" col2="4" start="284494" end="284497">#'  </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1222" col1="1" line2="1222" col2="65" start="284727" end="284791">#' The Wald test can be replaced with the \code{\link{nbinomLRT}}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1223" col1="1" line2="1223" col2="43" start="284960" end="285002">#' for an alternative test of significance.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1224" col1="1" line2="1224" col2="3" start="285193" end="285195">#' </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1225" col1="1" line2="1225" col2="39" start="285426" end="285464">#' Notes on the log2 fold change prior:</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1226" col1="1" line2="1226" col2="3" start="285659" end="285661">#' </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1227" col1="1" line2="1227" col2="50" start="285892" end="285941">#' The variance of the prior distribution for each</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1228" col1="1" line2="1228" col2="61" start="286125" end="286185">#' non-intercept coefficient is calculated using the observed</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1229" col1="1" line2="1229" col2="57" start="286358" end="286414">#' distribution of the maximum likelihood coefficients.  </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1230" col1="1" line2="1230" col2="65" start="286591" end="286655">#' The final coefficients are then maximum a posteriori estimates</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1231" col1="1" line2="1231" col2="53" start="286824" end="286876">#' using this prior (Tikhonov/ridge regularization). </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1232" col1="1" line2="1232" col2="31" start="287057" end="287087">#' See below for details on the</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1233" col1="1" line2="1233" col2="83" start="287290" end="287372">#' prior variance and the Methods section of the DESeq2 manuscript for more detail.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1234" col1="1" line2="1234" col2="78" start="287523" end="287600">#' The use of a prior has little effect on genes with high counts and helps to</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1235" col1="1" line2="1235" col2="71" start="287756" end="287826">#' moderate the large spread in coefficients for genes with low counts.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1236" col1="1" line2="1236" col2="2" start="287989" end="287990">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1237" col1="1" line2="1237" col2="71" start="288222" end="288292">#' The prior variance is calculated by matching the 0.05 upper quantile</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1238" col1="1" line2="1238" col2="75" start="288455" end="288529">#' of the observed MLE coefficients to a zero-centered Normal distribution.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1239" col1="1" line2="1239" col2="47" start="288688" end="288734">#' In a change of methods since the 2014 paper,</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1240" col1="1" line2="1240" col2="54" start="288921" end="288974">#' the weighted upper quantile is calculated using the</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1241" col1="1" line2="1241" col2="54" start="289154" end="289207">#' \code{wtd.quantile} function from the Hmisc package</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1242" col1="1" line2="1242" col2="70" start="289387" end="289456">#' (function has been copied into DESeq2 to avoid extra dependencies).</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1243" col1="1" line2="1243" col2="88" start="289620" end="289707">#' The weights are the inverse of the expected variance of log counts, so the inverse of</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1244" col1="1" line2="1244" col2="73" start="289853" end="289925">#' \eqn{1/\bar{\mu} + \alpha_{tr}}{1/mu-bar + alpha_tr} using the mean of</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1245" col1="1" line2="1245" col2="74" start="290086" end="290159">#' normalized counts and the trended dispersion fit. The weighting ensures</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1246" col1="1" line2="1246" col2="73" start="290319" end="290391">#' that noisy estimates of log fold changes from small count genes do not</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1247" col1="1" line2="1247" col2="58" start="290552" end="290609">#' overly influence the calculation of the prior variance.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1248" col1="1" line2="1248" col2="42" start="290785" end="290826">#' See \code{\link{estimateBetaPriorVar}}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1249" col1="1" line2="1249" col2="68" start="291018" end="291085">#' The final prior variance for a factor level is the average of the</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1250" col1="1" line2="1250" col2="76" start="291251" end="291326">#' estimated prior variance over all contrasts of all levels of the factor. </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1251" col1="1" line2="1251" col2="2" start="291484" end="291485">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1252" col1="1" line2="1252" col2="58" start="291717" end="291774">#' When a log2 fold change prior is used (betaPrior=TRUE),</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1253" col1="1" line2="1253" col2="74" start="291950" end="292023">#' then \code{nbinomWaldTest} will by default use expanded model matrices,</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1254" col1="1" line2="1254" col2="76" start="292183" end="292258">#' as described in the \code{modelMatrixType} argument, unless this argument</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1255" col1="1" line2="1255" col2="44" start="292416" end="292459">#' is used to override the default behavior.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1256" col1="1" line2="1256" col2="72" start="292649" end="292720">#' This ensures that log2 fold changes will be independent of the choice</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1257" col1="1" line2="1257" col2="76" start="292882" end="292957">#' of reference level. In this case, the beta prior variance for each factor</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1258" col1="1" line2="1258" col2="70" start="293115" end="293184">#' is calculated as the average of the mean squared maximum likelihood</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1259" col1="1" line2="1259" col2="57" start="293348" end="293404">#' estimates for each level and every possible contrast. </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1260" col1="1" line2="1260" col2="2" start="293581" end="293582">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1261" col1="1" line2="1261" col2="31" start="293814" end="293844">#' @param object a DESeqDataSet</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1262" col1="1" line2="1262" col2="69" start="294047" end="294115">#' @param betaPrior whether or not to put a zero-mean normal prior on</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1263" col1="1" line2="1263" col2="33" start="294280" end="294312">#' the non-intercept coefficients</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1264" col1="1" line2="1264" col2="66" start="294513" end="294578">#' @param betaPriorVar a vector with length equal to the number of</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1265" col1="1" line2="1265" col2="39" start="294746" end="294784">#' model terms including the intercept.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1266" col1="1" line2="1266" col2="67" start="294979" end="295045">#' betaPriorVar gives the variance of the prior on the sample betas</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1267" col1="1" line2="1267" col2="74" start="295212" end="295285">#' on the log2 scale. if missing (default) this is estimated from the data</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1268" col1="1" line2="1268" col2="71" start="295445" end="295515">#' @param modelMatrix an optional matrix, typically this is set to NULL</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1269" col1="1" line2="1269" col2="34" start="295678" end="295711">#' and created within the function</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1270" col1="1" line2="1270" col2="73" start="295911" end="295983">#' @param modelMatrixType either "standard" or "expanded", which describe</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1271" col1="1" line2="1271" col2="68" start="296144" end="296211">#' how the model matrix, X of the formula in \code{\link{DESeq}}, is</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1272" col1="1" line2="1272" col2="68" start="296377" end="296444">#' formed. "standard" is as created by \code{model.matrix} using the</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1273" col1="1" line2="1273" col2="69" start="296610" end="296678">#' design formula. "expanded" includes an indicator variable for each</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1274" col1="1" line2="1274" col2="48" start="296843" end="296890">#' level of factors in addition to an intercept.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1275" col1="1" line2="1275" col2="69" start="297076" end="297144">#' betaPrior must be set to TRUE in order for expanded model matrices</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1276" col1="1" line2="1276" col2="13" start="297309" end="297321">#' to be fit.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1277" col1="1" line2="1277" col2="56" start="297542" end="297597">#' @param betaTol control parameter defining convergence</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1278" col1="1" line2="1278" col2="80" start="297775" end="297854">#' @param maxit the maximum number of iterations to allow for convergence of the</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1279" col1="1" line2="1279" col2="21" start="298008" end="298028">#' coefficient vector</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1280" col1="1" line2="1280" col2="80" start="298241" end="298320">#' @param useOptim whether to use the native optim function on rows which do not</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1281" col1="1" line2="1281" col2="24" start="298474" end="298497">#' converge within maxit</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1282" col1="1" line2="1282" col2="54" start="298707" end="298760">#' @param quiet whether to print messages at each step</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1283" col1="1" line2="1283" col2="70" start="298940" end="299009">#' @param useT whether to use a t-distribution as a null distribution,</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1284" col1="1" line2="1284" col2="51" start="299173" end="299223">#' for significance testing of the Wald statistics.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1285" col1="1" line2="1285" col2="57" start="299406" end="299462">#' If FALSE, a standard normal null distribution is used.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1286" col1="1" line2="1286" col2="69" start="299639" end="299707">#' See next argument \code{df} for information about which t is used.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1287" col1="1" line2="1287" col2="66" start="299872" end="299937">#' If \code{useT=TRUE} then further calls to \code{\link{results}}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1288" col1="1" line2="1288" col2="71" start="300105" end="300175">#' will make use of \code{mcols(object)$tDegreesFreedom} that is stored</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1289" col1="1" line2="1289" col2="28" start="300338" end="300365">#' by \code{nbinomWaldTest}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1290" col1="1" line2="1290" col2="59" start="300571" end="300629">#' @param df the degrees of freedom for the t-distribution.</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="1553" col1="1" line2="1553" col2="47" start="361850" end="361896">#' Steps for estimating the beta prior variance</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1554" col1="1" line2="1554" col2="2" start="362083" end="362084">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1555" col1="1" line2="1555" col2="101" start="362316" end="362416">#' These lower-level functions are called within \code{\link{DESeq}} or \code{\link{nbinomWaldTest}}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1556" col1="1" line2="1556" col2="60" start="362549" end="362608">#' End users should use those higher-level function instead.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1557" col1="1" line2="1557" col2="82" start="362782" end="362863">#' NOTE: \code{estimateBetaPriorVar} returns a numeric vector, not a DESEqDataSet!</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1558" col1="1" line2="1558" col2="90" start="363015" end="363104">#' For advanced users: to use these functions, first run \code{estimateMLEForBetaPriorVar}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1559" col1="1" line2="1559" col2="44" start="363248" end="363291">#' and then run \code{estimateBetaPriorVar}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1560" col1="1" line2="1560" col2="2" start="363481" end="363482">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1561" col1="1" line2="1561" col2="31" start="363714" end="363744">#' @param object a DESeqDataSet</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1562" col1="1" line2="1562" col2="2" start="363947" end="363948">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1563" col1="1" line2="1563" col2="57" start="364180" end="364236">#' @param maxit as defined in \code{link{nbinomWaldTest}}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1564" col1="1" line2="1564" col2="60" start="364413" end="364472">#' @param useOptim as defined in \code{link{nbinomWaldTest}}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1565" col1="1" line2="1565" col2="57" start="364646" end="364702">#' @param useQR as defined in \code{link{nbinomWaldTest}}</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="1567" col1="1" line2="1567" col2="3" start="365112" end="365114">#' </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1568" col1="1" line2="1568" col2="77" start="365345" end="365421">#' @param betaPriorMethod the method for calculating the beta prior variance,</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1569" col1="1" line2="1569" col2="35" start="365578" end="365612">#' either "quanitle" or "weighted":</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1570" col1="1" line2="1570" col2="93" start="365811" end="365903">#' "quantile" matches a normal distribution using the upper quantile of the finite MLE betas.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1571" col1="1" line2="1571" col2="117" start="366044" end="366160">#' "weighted" matches a normal distribution using the upper quantile, but weighting by the variance of the MLE betas.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1572" col1="1" line2="1572" col2="61" start="366277" end="366337">#' @param upperQuantile the upper quantile to be used for the</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="1577" col1="1" line2="1577" col2="74" start="367442" end="367515">#' @return for \code{estimateMLEForBetaPriorVar}, a DESeqDataSet, with the</COMMENT>

  <COMMENT line1="1720" col1="1" line2="1720" col2="52" start="400761" end="400812">#' Likelihood ratio test (chi-squared test) for GLMs</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1721" col1="1" line2="1721" col2="2" start="400994" end="400995">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1722" col1="1" line2="1722" col2="71" start="401227" end="401297">#' This function tests for significance of change in deviance between a</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1723" col1="1" line2="1723" col2="63" start="401460" end="401522">#' full and reduced model which are provided as \code{formula}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1724" col1="1" line2="1724" col2="103" start="401693" end="401795">#' Fitting uses previously calculated \code{\link{sizeFactors}} (or \code{\link{normalizationFactors}})</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1725" col1="1" line2="1725" col2="28" start="401926" end="401953">#' and dispersion estimates.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1726" col1="1" line2="1726" col2="3" start="402159" end="402161">#' </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1727" col1="1" line2="1727" col2="71" start="402392" end="402462">#' The difference in deviance is compared to a chi-squared distribution</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1728" col1="1" line2="1728" col2="86" start="402625" end="402710">#' with df = (reduced residual degrees of freedom - full residual degrees of freedom).</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1729" col1="1" line2="1729" col2="91" start="402858" end="402948">#' This function is comparable to the \code{nbinomGLMTest} of the previous version of DESeq</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1730" col1="1" line2="1730" col2="66" start="403091" end="403156">#' and an alternative to the default \code{\link{nbinomWaldTest}}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1731" col1="1" line2="1731" col2="2" start="403324" end="403325">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1732" col1="1" line2="1732" col2="31" start="403557" end="403587">#' @param object a DESeqDataSet</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1733" col1="1" line2="1733" col2="68" start="403790" end="403857">#' @param full the full model formula, this should be the formula in</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1734" col1="1" line2="1734" col2="25" start="404023" end="404047">#' \code{design(object)}.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1735" col1="1" line2="1735" col2="33" start="404256" end="404288">#' alternatively, can be a matrix</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1736" col1="1" line2="1736" col2="60" start="404489" end="404548">#' @param reduced a reduced formula to compare against, e.g.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1737" col1="1" line2="1737" col2="59" start="404722" end="404780">#' the full model with a term or terms of interest removed.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1738" col1="1" line2="1738" col2="33" start="404955" end="404987">#' alternatively, can be a matrix</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1739" col1="1" line2="1739" col2="56" start="405188" end="405243">#' @param betaTol control parameter defining convergence</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1740" col1="1" line2="1740" col2="80" start="405421" end="405500">#' @param maxit the maximum number of iterations to allow for convergence of the</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1741" col1="1" line2="1741" col2="21" start="405654" end="405674">#' coefficient vector</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1742" col1="1" line2="1742" col2="80" start="405887" end="405966">#' @param useOptim whether to use the native optim function on rows which do not</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1743" col1="1" line2="1743" col2="24" start="406120" end="406143">#' converge within maxit</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1744" col1="1" line2="1744" col2="54" start="406353" end="406406">#' @param quiet whether to print messages at each step</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1745" col1="1" line2="1745" col2="65" start="406586" end="406650">#' @param useQR whether to use the QR decomposition on the design</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1746" col1="1" line2="1746" col2="33" start="406819" end="406851">#' matrix X while fitting the GLM</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1747" col1="1" line2="1747" col2="72" start="407052" end="407123">#' @param minmu lower bound on the estimated count while fitting the GLM</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1748" col1="1" line2="1748" col2="74" start="407285" end="407358">#' @param type either "DESeq2" or "glmGamPoi". If \code{type = "DESeq2"} a</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1749" col1="1" line2="1749" col2="75" start="407518" end="407592">#' classical likelihood ratio test based on the Chi-squared distribution is</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1750" col1="1" line2="1750" col2="76" start="407751" end="407826">#' conducted. If \code{type = "glmGamPoi"} and previously the dispersion has</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1751" col1="1" line2="1751" col2="77" start="407984" end="408060">#' been estimated with glmGamPoi as well, a quasi-likelihood ratio test based</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1752" col1="1" line2="1752" col2="82" start="408217" end="408298">#' on the F-distribution is conducted. It is supposed to be more accurate, because</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1753" col1="1" line2="1753" col2="79" start="408450" end="408528">#' it takes the uncertainty of dispersion estimate into account in the same way</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1754" col1="1" line2="1754" col2="40" start="408683" end="408722">#' that a t-test improves upon a Z-test.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1755" col1="1" line2="1755" col2="3" start="408916" end="408918">#' </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1756" col1="1" line2="1756" col2="61" start="409149" end="409209">#' @return a DESeqDataSet with new results columns accessible</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1757" col1="1" line2="1757" col2="85" start="409382" end="409466">#' with the \code{\link{results}} function.  The coefficients and standard errors are</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1758" col1="1" line2="1758" col2="28" start="409615" end="409642">#' reported on a log2 scale.</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1759" col1="1" line2="1759" col2="3" start="409848" end="409850">#' </COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1760" col1="1" line2="1760" col2="61" start="410081" end="410141">#' @seealso \code{\link{DESeq}}, \code{\link{nbinomWaldTest}}</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1761" col1="1" line2="1761" col2="2" start="410314" end="410315">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1762" col1="1" line2="1762" col2="12" start="410547" end="410558">#' @examples</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1763" col1="1" line2="1763" col2="2" start="410780" end="410781">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1764" col1="1" line2="1764" col2="35" start="411013" end="411047">#' dds &lt;- makeExampleDESeqDataSet()</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1765" col1="1" line2="1765" col2="34" start="411246" end="411279">#' dds &lt;- estimateSizeFactors(dds)</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1766" col1="1" line2="1766" col2="34" start="411479" end="411512">#' dds &lt;- estimateDispersions(dds)</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1767" col1="1" line2="1767" col2="39" start="411712" end="411750">#' dds &lt;- nbinomLRT(dds, reduced = ~ 1)</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1768" col1="1" line2="1768" col2="22" start="411945" end="411966">#' res &lt;- results(dds)</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1769" col1="1" line2="1769" col2="2" start="412178" end="412179">#'</COMMENT>
  <COMMENT line1="1770" col1="1" line2="1770" col2="10" start="412411" end="412420">#' @export</COMMENT>
  <expr line1="1771" col1="1" line2="1996" col2="1" start="412644" end="465069">
    <expr line1="1771" col1="1" line2="1771" col2="9" start="412644" end="412652">
      <SYMBOL line1="1771" col1="1" line2="1771" col2="9" start="412644" end="412652">nbinomLRT</SYMBOL>
    </expr>
    <LEFT_ASSIGN line1="1771" col1="11" line2="1771" col2="12" start="412654" end="412655">&lt;-</LEFT_ASSIGN>
    <expr line1="1771" col1="14" line2="1996" col2="1" start="412657" end="465069">
      <FUNCTION line1="1771" col1="14" line2="1771" col2="21" start="412657" end="412664">function</FUNCTION>
      <OP-LEFT-PAREN line1="1771" col1="22" line2="1771" col2="22" start="412665" end="412665">(</OP-LEFT-PAREN>

      <OP-COMMA line1="1771" col1="29" line2="1771" col2="29" start="412672" end="412672">,</OP-COMMA>

      <expr line1="1771" col1="36" line2="1771" col2="49" start="412679" end="412692">
        <expr line1="1771" col1="36" line2="1771" col2="41" start="412679" end="412684">
          <SYMBOL_FUNCTION_CALL line1="1771" col1="36" line2="1771" col2="41" start="412679" end="412684">design</SYMBOL_FUNCTION_CALL>

        <OP-LEFT-PAREN line1="1771" col1="42" line2="1771" col2="42" start="412685" end="412685">(</OP-LEFT-PAREN>
        <expr line1="1771" col1="43" line2="1771" col2="48" start="412686" end="412691">

        <OP-RIGHT-PAREN line1="1771" col1="49" line2="1771" col2="49" start="412692" end="412692">)</OP-RIGHT-PAREN>
      </expr>
      <OP-COMMA line1="1771" col1="50" line2="1771" col2="50" start="412693" end="412693">,</OP-COMMA>
      <SYMBOL_FORMALS line1="1771" col1="52" line2="1771" col2="58" start="412695" end="412701">reduced</SYMBOL_FORMALS>
